ia `StatusWriter.Log()` method (lines 196, 91)\n   - This sends JSON-encoded `StatusMessage` with type `MsgLog` to the agent's stdout\n   - **BUT this only happens during step execution, not for LLM raw output**\n\n3. **Daemon Side Collection** (`internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`):\n   - The daemon attaches to container stdout and parses JSON status messages (lines 191-251)\n   - When it sees a `MsgLog` message, it publishes to the `logBroadcast` broadcaster (lines 207-215)\n   - **The issue: `MsgLog` messages contain only extracted/parsed text, not the full raw Claude output**\n   - For agent steps, `StatusWriter.Log()` is only called with parsed/extracted lines during execution\n   - Raw Claude JSON output is captured into a buffer but not streamed—only written to disk at step end\n\n4. **Client-Side Consumption**:\n   - **For active runs**: Web/gRPC clients subscribe to `logBroadcast` (line 847) and receive live `LogLine` messages\n   - **For completed runs**: `StreamLogs` RPC reads the archived `full.log` file (lines 466-486) and streams it line-by-line\n\n### **Key Architecture Files**\n\n| File | Purpose | Issue Relevance |\n|------|---------|-----------------|\n| `/workspace/internal/ports/agent.go` | **AgentAdapter interface** - simple Execute(ctx, step, workDir) -> (result, error) | No streaming support in interface |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go` | **Claude Code adapter** - lines 158-217 stream via scanner but only write parsed text | Raw Claude JSON not streamed |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/generic/generic.go` | **Script adapter** - lines 74-96 stream output via StatusWriter | Works but limited to single-line output |\n| `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go` | **In-container executor** - orchestrates steps, creates `logStream.Writer`, buffers output | Lines 140-141: Logs output AFTER step finishes |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` | **Daemon gRPC server** - lines 191-251 attach to container, parse status messages | Lines 207-215: Only publishes parsed log lines, not raw streaming |\n| `/workspace/internal/logstream/logstream.go` | **Unified log writer** - buffered file appender | Write-only, doesn't broadcast |\n| `/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go` | **Live broadcaster** - fans out LogLine to subscribers | Works but receives data late |\n| `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` | **gRPC streaming definition** - `StreamLogs` RPC | Returns stream of LogEntry messages after run completes |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` | **Web SSE streaming** - lines 808-871 handle active/completed run streaming | Lines 832-838: Completed runs served from archived logs |\n\n### **The Bottleneck Points**\n\n1. **Step Executor writes logs AFTER execution completes** (runner.go:140-141)\n   - `logStepOutput()` reads from disk after step finishes\n   - Only then written to unified `full.log`\n\n2. **StatusWriter.Log() is not connected to raw Claude output** (prompt.go:196)\n   - Live log lines sent via StatusWriter are parsed/extracted text only\n   - Raw Claude JSON output (containing full streaming) goes to a buffer\n   - Buffer only written to file after step completes (prompt.go:123)\n\n3. **Daemon receives logs too late** (grpc/server.go:207)\n   - Messages only come through after they're written to files\n   - No way to intercept raw Claude output stream before buffering\n\n4. **gRPC StreamLogs serves archived logs only** (cloche.proto:10, server.go:447-614)\n   - No live streaming path that reads directly from container stdout\n   - Filtered logs require step to be complete and output extracted (line 457-459)\n\n### **Why Logs Don't Stream Live**\n\nThe fundamental issue is **architectural**: The current system:\n- Buffers entire step output in memory/buffer\n- Writes complete output to file after step finishes\n- Then reads file back and broadcasts it\n\nThis creates a \"all-or-nothing\" delivery where subscribers get either:\n- Nothing (if run is active), OR\n- Everything at once (when reading archived `full.log`)\n\n**Live streaming for active runs only works if the broadcaster received data as it was produced, but currently it only gets data after the step completes.**"}],"totalDurationMs":46272,"totalTokens":58379,"totalToolUseCount":30,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1268,"cache_read_input_tokens":55631,"output_tokens":1477,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1268},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
