nd calls `StatusWriter.Log()` when a newline appears, which writes JSON to stdout for Docker to capture and the daemon to read.\n\nBut I'm wondering if there's a buffering issue somewhere in this chain, or maybe the problem is actually on the web handler or SSE delivery side rather than in the log emission itself. Let me reconsider whether `extractStreamText()` is properly pulling the right content from the stream.\n\nActually, let me look at how the `generic.Adapter` handles streaming for script steps too.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":796,"cache_read_input_tokens":49069,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":796},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"be03ba05-685d-4063-a5b5-3cada1f11f8c","uuid":"626bf3be-0803-4b24-9282-680ad2ac33fc"}
