[2026-03-10T21:50:57Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017bYGCJMjE3of2Per9v64yH","type":"tool_result","content":"   900→// parseLLMLogLine parses a LogLine whose type is \"llm\". If the content is\n   901→// Claude stream JSON, it extracts the human-readable text. Protocol-only\n   902→// events return a LogLine with an empty Type (caller should skip it).\n   903→// Non-llm lines are returned unchanged.\n   904→func parseLLMLogLine(line logstream.LogLine) logstream.LogLine {\n   905→\tif line.Type != \"llm\" {\n   906→\t\treturn line\n   907→\t}\n   908→\ttext, ok := logstream.ParseClaudeLine([]byte(line.Content))\n   909→\tif !ok {\n   910→\t\treturn logstream.LogLine{} // signal to skip\n   911→\t}\n   912→\tline.Content = text\n   913→\treturn line\n   914→}\n   915→\n   916→// parseFullLogLine parses a \"[timestamp] [type] content\" line into a LogLine.\n   917→func parseFullLogLine(text string) logstream.LogLine {\n   918→\tm := logLineRegex.FindStringSubmatch(text)\n   919→\tif m == nil {\n   920→\t\treturn logstream.LogLine{\n   921→\t\t\tTimestamp: time.Now().UTC().Format(time.RFC3339),\n   922→\t\t\tType:      \"script\",\n   923→\t\t\tContent:   text,\n   924→\t\t}\n   925→\t}\n   926→\treturn logstream.LogLine{\n   927→\t\tTimestamp: m[1],\n   928→\t\tType:      m[2],\n   929→\t\tContent:   m[3],"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"be03ba05-685d-4063-a5b5-3cada1f11f8c","uuid":"3c5d8141-2b3e-4542-a0fd-f2552c3775f0","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go","content":"// parseLLMLogLine parses a LogLine whose type is \"llm\". If the content is\n// Claude stream JSON, it extracts the human-readable text. Protocol-only\n// events return a LogLine with an empty Type (caller should skip it).\n// Non-llm lines are returned unchanged.\nfunc parseLLMLogLine(line logstream.LogLine) logstream.LogLine {\n\tif line.Type != \"llm\" {\n\t\treturn line\n\t}\n\ttext, ok := logstream.ParseClaudeLine([]byte(line.Content))\n\tif !ok {\n\t\treturn logstream.LogLine{} // signal to skip\n\t}\n\tline.Content = text\n\treturn line\n}\n\n// parseFullLogLine parses a \"[timestamp] [type] content\" line into a LogLine.\nfunc parseFullLogLine(text string) logstream.LogLine {\n\tm := logLineRegex.FindStringSubmatch(text)\n\tif m == nil {\n\t\treturn logstream.LogLine{\n\t\t\tTimestamp: time.Now().UTC().Format(time.RFC3339),\n\t\t\tType:      \"script\",\n\t\t\tContent:   text,\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn logstream.LogLine{\n\t\tTimestamp: m[1],\n\t\tType:      m[2],\n\t\tContent:   m[3],","numLines":30,"startLine":900,"totalLines":1448}}}
[2026-03-10T21:50:57Z] [llm] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01AaZi37TzGJHwYs28q21uem","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see something important. The `parseLLMLogLine` function in the SSE handler checks if `line.Type == \"llm\"` and then parses it. For live streaming lines, the broadcaster publishes with `Type: \"llm\"` and `Content: msg.Message` where `msg.Message` is the extracted text from the prompt adapter.\n\nBut `parseLLMLogLine` calls `logstream.ParseClaudeLine([]byte(line.Content))` - this is trying to parse Claude stream JSON from a line that's already been extracted as plain text! The content from the live stream is already human-readable text (extracted from stream-json by `extractStreamText` in prompt.go), not raw Claude JSON.\n\n\nSo when `ParseClaudeLine` tries to parse plain text as JSON, it fails and returns `ok=false`, causing `parseLLMLogLine` to return an empty `LogLine{}` that the SSE handler skips entirely. That's the bug - the live-streamed content is already extracted text, but we're trying to parse it as raw Claude stream-json and discarding it when that fails. Let me check what `ParseClaudeLine` actually does to confirm.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":516,"cache_read_input_tokens":54938,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":516},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"be03ba05-685d-4063-a5b5-3cada1f11f8c","uuid":"f4020583-33b5-47a2-b29e-5a9fb8bb6b3e"}
